      <TD bgcolor="#94D6E7" colspan=4><font size="+2">&nbsp;INTRODUCTION</font></TD>
   </TR>
   <TR>
<TD colspan=4><font size="+1"><br>SNPs discovery is important for detection, forensic analysis and for understanding 
the genetic variations among closely related microorganisms. <b><i>SNPsFinder</i></b> is a web-based program developed 
to facilitate the SNPs discovery process. Complete genomic sequences or contig sequences of related organisms (strains and 
species) can be used for this analysis. In additon to identification of the SNPs regions, primers can be picked automaticly
 according to user-defined parameters to assist in experimental validation of the predicted SNPs. Results from <b><i>SNPsFinder</i></b> analysis can be viewed through WWW. 
Click <a href="./UsersManual/index.html" target=_blank>HERE</a> for User's Manual.<br><br></font>
      </TD>
   </TR>
